thread.title: Major League Soccer power rankings, 10/21: Portland Timbers make their move
thread.title_full: Major League Soccer power rankings, 10/21: Portland Timbers make their move | The Seattle Times

author: Matt Pentz
title: Major League Soccer power rankings, 10/21: Portland Timbers make their move
text:
Two straight wins, first at Salt Lake then a five-goal stunner in L.A., have lifted the Timbers into fourth place in the West and all the way into fifth in my weekly power rankings. Last week’s ranking in parentheses. 
1. New York Red Bulls (1) Shield comes down to the final week. Form: L-W-W-L-W. Up next: at Chicago on Sunday. 2. Dallas (2) Already locked up home-field advantage in West. Form: L-W-D-W-W. Up next: vs. San Jose. 3. Columbus (7) Played best game of season at Toronto. Form: W-W-L-L-W. Up next: vs. D.C. on Sunday. 4. Los Angeles (3) Apparently not invincible at home. Form: L-D-W-D-L. Up next: at Kansas City on Sunday. 5. Portland (13) Where in the world did that come from? Form: L-W-L-W-W. Up next: vs. Colorado on Sunday. 6. Montreal (9) This team is on fire. Form: W-L-L-W-W. Up next: vs. Toronto on Sunday. 7. D.C. (11) Just like that, back in second place. Form: D-L-L-W-W. Up next: at Columbus on Sunday. 8. Kansas City (4) Wednesday’s game in hand is huge. Form: W-D-L-W-L. Up next: vs. Colorado on Wednesday. 9. Toronto (10) Long playoff wait is over. Form: W-W-W-W-L. Up next: at Montreal on Sunday. 10. Vancouver (6) Looking like a team with a ceiling. Form: L-L-D-D-L. Up next: vs. Houston on Sunday. 11. New England (5) The Revs have fooled me more than once. Form: W-L-D-L-L. Up next: vs. New York City FC on Sunday. 12. Seattle (8) Looked inexplicably listless in Houston. Form: D-W-D-D-D. Up next: vs. Salt Lake on Sunday. 13. San Jose (12) Needs a win and some help. Form: D-L-W-D-W. Up next: at Dallas on Sunday. 14. Orlando (15) Raging in vain against dying light. Form: W-W-W-W-W. Up next: at Philadelphia. 15. Salt Lake (14) Lengthy postseason streak comes to an end. Form: W-L-W-L-L. Up next: at Seattle on Sunday. 16. Houston (16) Showed very little desperation against Seattle. Form: L-W-W-L-D. Up next: at Vancouver on Sunday. 17. New York City FC (17) 10 points out of the race. Form: W-W-W-L-L. Up next: vs. New England on Sunday. 18. Colorado (20) Rises a few spots by default. Form: D-L-L-L-L Up next: at Kansas City on Wednesday. 19. Philadelphia (18) Waved the white flag at Red Bull Arena. Form: L-W-D-L-L. Up next: vs. Orlando City on Sunday. 20. Chicago (19) Rolled over and died at RFK Stadium.. Form: L-L-L-W-L. Up next: vs. New York Red Bulls on Sunday. Matt Pentz : 206-464-3184 or mpentz@seattletimes.com ; on Twitter: @mattpentz . Matt Pentz covers Sounders FC, Reign FC, MLS and world soccer for The Seattle Times throughout the year.
